caption.text:
[Summer Highlights]

Feel super lucky that I was able to participate in one of the coolest summer program in South Korea; Global Collaborative Program 2017 held by Kyung Hee University. I gained countless amount of new knowledge and insights,met so many heartwarming friends and great professors from various countries.

One of the courses that i took was an IR related course named "Can the World be Governed". A course taught by our so-called "superstar prof" namely John Ikenberry who came all the way from Princeton University, New Jersey. Glad that I have had a chance to attend his lectures during this summer semester. He never fails to amaze us with his inspiring stories.

I also took Korean Language class and u can easily tell just how fun it was to learn a new language with other students coming from different countries and to hear them speaking in Korean with their own kinds of accent.

These are the pics that we took during the last lectures, when we were about to have our farewell.

Glad and sad at the same time but it was such an extremely valuable experience indeed!

Arriate is one of those must-visit Cafes in Seoul as it offers such a relaxing atmosphere with a room full of beautiful flowers and herbs. It's a nice choice of cafe destination to spend some time of enjoying a cup of herbal tea or coffee, and eating some nice cakes. Arriate is so easy to find as its located just a few blocks away from exit 9 of Hongik Station. 
#VisitSeoul #GlobalSeoulMate #Seoul

I went to 6th floor of Humanitas College building of Kyung Hee University yesterday and was so enchanted when i finally got to see for the first time this mesmerizing scenery of the campus in cherry blossom season. Located in Dongdaemun-gu, KHU is one of those attractive tourist destinations especially during spring. With gothic-style buildings and bunch of pinky cherryblossoms, it's a great place not only to study, but also to enjoy time with our loved ones, have picnics and take lots of pictures! 
In fact, I'm now studying at this beautiful campus for 2 semesters as an exchange student and it really feels like a dream come true.
